added.title: Booty Eggs
added.description: Not wanting to be creeped out on Easter the Titans dispatch the Easter Bunny and take matters into their own hands.

added.title: TV Knight 4
added.description: Batman and Commissioner Gordon go camping but instead of fun outdoor activities they'd rather watch TV.

added.title: Lil' Dimples
added.description: Thinking it's a way to reconnect with her father, Raven enters a beauty pageant.

added.title: Don't Be An Icarus
added.description: Robin tries to tell some Greek myths but the other Titans give their own fractured versions instead.

added.title: The Lesson
added.description: Gumball and Darwin get put in detention and quickly find it's more like prison than school. And there's only one thing to do in prison... ESCAPE!

added.title: The Game
added.description: The Wattersons embark on their first family game of Dodge or Dare, but soon find out why Gumball and Darwin abandoned the monster they created.

added.title: The Limit
added.description: The Watterson family faces Mom's wrath in a supermarket.

added.title: The Promise
added.description: Darwin has promised to play video games with Gumball, but there is a Banana Joe-shaped problem...

added.title: The Kid From 3030
added.description: The kids meet a mysterious kid from the future and try to help him complete his mission.

added.title: Power Punchers
added.description: Fed up with losing in video games to his Dad, Craig seeks training in the Creek.

added.title: Creek Cart Racers
added.description: A high-speed race with a high-stakes prize may be too much for Craig and his friends.

added.title: Secret Book Club
added.description: Kelsey starts a super secret book club to introduce Craig and JP to the joys of reading.

added.title: Jextra Perrestrial
added.description: JP believes he may be from another planet, so Craig tries to help him make contact.

added.title: Charlie Ball
added.description: After Panda gets injured on the basketball court, the Bears invite Charlie to be on their basketball team. But when Charlie gets too good, he starts to ruin all the fun of the game.

added.title: Yard Sale
added.description: Each of the Bears get offbeat items at a local yard sale. Their new possessions send them on their own separate adventures.

added.title: Slumber Party
added.description: A thunderstorm forces Chloe to spend the night at the Cave with the Bears. When Chloe's parents tell the Bears to protect Chloe, they take the task a bit too seriously.

added.title: Bear Cleanse
added.description: A doctor tells the Bears to go on a cleanse to improve their health. But when Grizz realizes he can only eat what grizzly bears eat, he starts to lose his mind.

added.title: Nom Nom's Entourage
added.description: Nom Nom recruits the Bears to act as his entourage of friends. But when the Bears realize Nom Nom doesn't understand friendship, they decide to kick their day of bonding into high gear.

added.title: Hustlecup
added.description: When Buttercup loses the Professor's latest invention, she'll have to beat The Gangreen Gang at their own game to get it back.

added.title: Rebel Rebel
added.description: The Professor makes new friends, but they may be the wrong crowd.

added.title: Our Brand is Chaos
added.description: Bubbles and Buttercup make a deal without realizing the consequences.

added.title: Tagalong
added.description: Buttercup is tired of Bubbles following her everywhere.

added.title: Brainlord
added.description: A new superhero arrives in Townsville with a dark secret.

added.title: Together Alone
added.description: Steven throws a party to bring his family together.

added.title: Escapism
added.description: Steven uses his psychic powers to find help.

added.title: Change Your Mind
added.description: Steven faces his biggest challenge yet.

added.title: Laser Light Cannon
added.description: A magical comet hurtles toward Beach City, and Steven must dig through his father's collection of old junk, and the past, to find the weapon that can save the town.

added.title: Cheeseburger Backpack
added.description: A mission to the Lunar Sea Spire takes a treacherous turn, but Steven has packed his totally amazing Cheeseburger Backpack with anything they could ever need!

added.title: The Other Tarts
added.description: Finn and Jake volunteer for a dangerous assignment: currying rare tarts for a meeting of Ooo royalty.

added.title: To Cut a Woman's Hair
added.description: Finn needs to find a princess willing to give up a lock of her hair to save Jake from a balding witch.

added.title: The Pods
added.description: Finn and Jake must sort out the good magic beans from the bad.

added.title: The Chamber of Frozen Blades
added.description: In Ninja-mode, Finn and Jake break into Ice King's palace to catch him red-handed.

added.title: The Silent King
added.description: Finn and Jake get to live like royalty, but soon fine the easy life doesn't suit them. Or at least not Finn.

added.title: Trailer Trashed
added.description: Muscle Man's trailer fails a health inspection and he wants to keep it at all costs.

added.title: Meteor Moves
added.description: Mordecai wants to finally kiss Margaret at a meteor shower.

added.title: Family BBQ
added.description: Mordecai wants to get a handshake from Margaret's dad.

added.title: The Last Laserdisc Player
added.description: Mordecai, Rigby, Muscle Man and HFG want to get a laserdisc player so they can watch the director's cut of a cult classic.

added.title: Country Club
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to rescue the golf cart from a bunch of rich people at a country club.

added.title: Bucky and the Howl
added.description: After Clarence learns Sumo's in the school musical, he joins up and enthusiastically promotes the show. On opening night with a packed house, stage fright takes hold of Sumo and he runs off leaving Clarence to go on alone.

added.title: Worm Bin
added.description: After his mom gets a worm bin, Jeff deals with the gross reality that he has a tub of bugs living in his kitchen, and Clarence obsesses over feeding the worms.

added.title: Clarence and Sumo's Rexcellent Adventure
added.description: On a school trip to the Aberdale Natural History Museum, Clarence and Sumo check out the displays, goof around with the exhibits and even remove a tooth from the T-Rex display.

added.title: Birthday
added.description: Jeff and Sumo expect no one to show at Clarence's birthday party, just like last year. When dozens of kids arrive, the boys struggle to get face time with Clarence, the popular party host.

added.title: Plant Daddies
added.description: When Ms. Baker pairs up the kids to act as parents for a sprout, Sumo and Clarence learn all about good parenting. Jeff buys toys instead of fertilizer and Chelsea and Kimby get to know each other.

added.title: Mystery Noise
added.description: It's Sleepover Dream Night in the RV and the gang just wants to get some sleep to dream their dreams, but when a mysterious noise keeps them awake, their grip on sanity begins slipping.

added.title: Charlie Burgers
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and crew help a friendly dog, Charlie Burgers, find his lost ball by literally turning the world upside down.

added.title: Shorts
added.description: A collection of shorts where Uncle Grandpa and the gang host a news program that goes awry, two turtles decide whether things are cool or dumb, and Uncle Grandpa goes on an accidental rampage trying to hit a pinata.

added.title: Perfect Kid
added.description: Uncle Grandpa helps a kid become perfect by turning him into a robot.  But when the robot tries to destroy him for being imperfect, Uncle Grandpa goes on the run.

added.title: Big in Japan
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa and the gang help a kid make a giant monster movie, they cast Mr. Gus as the monster.  But things get tense on the set when Mr. Gus wants to flex his acting muscles while Uncle Grandpa only wants him to flex his monster muscles.

added.title: The Voice
added.description: When Gumball and Darwin receive a scary email, everyone is a suspect... including themselves!
